   FEDERAL JUDICIARY SITES

   U.S. Courts Home Page
   http://www.uscourts.gov
   Contains links to all federal court web sites.

   Federal Judicial Center
   http://www.fjc.gov
   The education arm of the federal judiciary

   United States Sentencing Commission
   http:\\www.ussc.gov
   Includes member list, annual reports, manuals, and other documents

   Commission on Structural Alternatives for the Federal Courts of Appeal
   http://app.comm.uscourts.gov
   Final report on suggestions to address growing caseload of federal
   courts of appeal, specifically the ninth circuit.

   U.S. Supreme Court Home Page

   http://supremecourtus.gov

   Official U.S. Supreme Court site.  Contains information about the
   court, calendars, rules, filing guides, and press releases.  Opinions
   starting with 1999 court year.  Docket information forthcoming.

   Supreme Court Decisions
   http://supct.law.cornell.edu/supct/index.html
   Links to Supreme Court opinions, court calendar, current schedule of
   oral arguments, information on former and current justices, Supreme
   Court rules, and other Supreme Court information.

   Briefserve.com

   http://www.briefserve.com

   Commercial source for Supreme Court petitions and briefs.  Free
   information includes court calendars, rules, forms, guides, and
   Questions Presented.  Downloaded petitions and briefs  (PDF format) for
   $25 each.

   The Oyez Project, Northwestern University
   http://oyez.nwu.edu
   A multimedia site that includes oral arguments via RealAudio downloads.

   FLITE (Supreme Court decisions 1937-1975)
   http://www.fedworld.gov/supcourt/index.htm
   http://supct.law.cornell.edu/supct

   Status of Nominations in  Current Congress

   http://www.senate.gov/legislative/legis_act_nominations.html


   Federal Rules of Procedure
   This page has links to rules in effect, proposed amendments, local
   rules of courts, and rules committee records.
   http://www.uscourts.gov/rules/
